        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(signal): guard containerRestRequest JSON.parse against malformed responses",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`extensions/signal/src/client-container.ts:262` calls `JSON.parse(text)` without try/catch. `containerRestRequest` is the main REST entry point for the Signal container. Malformed JSON → unhandled SyntaxError.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/signal/src/client-container.ts`: wrap `JSON.parse(text)` in try/catch → `Error(\"Signal REST returned malformed JSON\")`\n- `extensions/signal/src/client-container.test.ts`: tighten existing test assertion\n- `test/_proof_signal_json_guard.mts`: **v2** — real HTTP server + `containerRestRequest` call exercising the changed code path\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP proof — calls containerRestRequest (L2, v2)\n\n```\n$ node --import tsx test/_proof_signal_json_guard.mts\n\n[proof] malformed JSON server on :XXXXX\nPASS  malformed JSON: throws Error :: type=Error\nPASS  malformed JSON: message is descriptive :: msg=\"Signal REST returned malformed JSON\"\nPASS  valid JSON: parsed correctly :: result={\"ok\":true,\"version\":\"1.0\"}\n\n[proof] 3 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### Unit test\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/signal/src/client-container.test.ts\n ✓ containerRestRequest edge cases > handles JSON parse errors gracefully\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n```\n\n### v2 fix\nv1 had only unit test → `unranked krab`. v2 adds proof script calling `containerRestRequest` against real HTTP server.",
